## Quick Start (2 minutes)

### For the Impatient

```bash
# Navigate to LEARN directory
cd ~/LEARN

# List all lessons
learn --list

# Open your first lesson (C++, Level 1)
learn c++ 1

# Immediately you'll see:
# - Left pane: lesson content (what to learn)
# - Right pane: code editor (where to write)
```

### Inside Neovim

```vim
gg                      Jump to top of lesson
G                       Jump to bottom
/Learning Goals         Search for concepts
n                       Find next match

C-l                     Move to code pane
i                       Start typing your code
:w                      Save when done

:terminal               Open terminal for testing
gcc solution.c -o solution && ./solution
exit                    Return to editor

:call NextLesson()      Jump to next level
```

