## Your Typical Learning Session

```vim
# Start a session
$ nvim

# Step 1: Open lesson in left buffer
:vsplit ../../c-c++/stage-1/level-1/lesson.md
:set readonly " Don't accidentally edit the lesson

# Step 2: Open code template in right buffer
:e solution.c
:r TEMPLATES/code-template.c " Insert boilerplate

# Step 3: Navigate and code
" Use Vim movements to jump between lesson concepts
gg " Go to top of lesson
/Learning Goals " Search for section
} " Jump to next section
ma " Mark important concept

" Switch to right buffer
C-w l " Focus right window
" ... write your code ...

# Step 4: Compile and test
:terminal
gcc solution.c -o solution && ./solution

# Step 5: Mark completion
" Switch back to lesson buffer
C-w h
:call LessonMarkComplete() " Custom function (in config)
```

