## Essential Vim Concepts for Learning

These are the Vim patterns you'll use repeatedly:

### Window Management
```vim
:vsplit " Open lesson | code side-by-side
C-w l " Move to right window
C-w h " Move to left window
C-w = " Equal width windows
C-w | " Full width for current
C-w 20 " Make window 20 columns wide
```

### Buffer Navigation
```vim
:bnext / :bn " Next buffer
:bprev / :bp " Previous buffer
C-^ " Toggle between last two buffers
:ls " List open buffers
:b1 " Go to buffer 1
```

### Marking Progress
```vim
ma " Mark position 'a'
`a " Jump to mark 'a'
:marks " View all marks
```

### Searching in Lessons
```vim
/pattern " Search forward
?pattern " Search backward
n " Next match
N " Previous match
* " Search word under cursor
```

### Recording & Replaying
```vim
qa " Start recording macro 'a'
" ... your commands ...
q " Stop recording
@a " Play macro 'a'
@@ or 2@a " Repeat macro
```

